Knock knock! Jet and I might be showing up at your door to deliver holiday treats. With the help of @Truvia Sweet Complete Granulated All-Purpose Sweetener, I made some candied nuts to get into the holiday spirit. Super simple to make and you can add your own twist! Truvia Sweet Complete Sweeteners have zero-calories per serving, and bakes and browns in recipes just like sugar.
 
For every 1 cup of nuts you’ll need, 1/4 cup of #Truvia Sweet Complete (measures cup for cup like sugar) and 1 tablespoon of butter. 
 
Add to a skillet over medium heat and stir constantly. You’ll only need about 5 minutes before you see the mixture start to liquify. Try adding cinnamon, sea salt or nutmeg to spice them up!
 
Are you team salty or sweet?

Important Safety Information 

Afrezza® (insulin human) Inhalation Powder may cause serious side effects, including sudden lung problems, low blood sugar, decreased lung function, lung cancer, diabetic ketoacidosis, severe allergic reaction, low potassium in your blood and heart failure. Some these side effects may lead to death. The most common side effects are low blood sugar, cough, and sore throat. Do not use AFREZZA if you have long-term lung problems such as asthma or chronic obstructive pulmonary disease. AFREZZA is not for use in place of long-acting insulin. AFREZZA must be used with long-acting insulin in people who have type 1 diabetes mellitus. AFREZZA is not for use in people who smoke or have recently stopped smoking (less than 6 months) AFREZZA is used to control high blood sugar in adults with diabetes mellitus.

Please see Full Prescribing Information, including BOXED WARNING, Medication Guide and Instructions for Use on Afrezza.com/Safety.

Did you know May is National Strawberry Month??🍓🍓🍓

 I used @truvia to make a simple, delicious and low calorie jam! You can use this jam on crackers, for breakfast or to spread sweetness to family and friends! Recipe below: 
 
8-10 oz of diced strawberries 
1/4 cup Truvia Stevia Sweetener
1/4 cup water
Lemon wedge 
(& if you want to thicken the jam, you can use chia seeds 1 tbsp at a time until desired consistency) 
 
Add all ingredients on medium heat. Stir & mash until your desired consistency is reached. Turn to low & simmer for about 15 mins.  
How do you enjoy strawberry jam? 🍓

@apachelakeresort photo dump! 

This place was magical. It is TRULY a hidden gem. A little difficult to get to but worth it! My entire family enjoyed & we will definitely return before the summer ends. 

Highlights: 
☀️only lake in central AZ with lakeside hotel rooms 
☀️has rentals ON property. Pontoons, kayaks, paddleboards ☀️staff felt like family. Very kind & helpful! 

This is def a place where you would go to enjoy a more relaxed vacation. We packed all our food as if we were camping. There is no Wi-Fi. We spent our days not worried about the time. Went out onto the water & stayed outside grilling & relaxing until the sun went down. 

I have so much more to share but if you want to visit you can use code “GLITTERGLUCOSE” for a discount on your room!

I picked out the perfect watermelon at @frysfoodstores! I’m celebrating #NationalWatermelonDay! Here are 3 tips for picking the best watermelon🍉 

❤️Look for a yellow field spot! This shows where the watermelon sat on the ground as it ripened. 
❤️Look for dark green stripes. 
❤️Knock on it. If it sounds deep and hollow that means there’s more water & is riper.

#Ad Green means GO! But do you know what to do if you test positive or experience COVID-19 symptoms? It's important to KNOW whether you have a high-risk factor that could make your illness from the virus more severe. Having diabetes like myself, being age 50+ or having asthma are just some of the factors that can put you at high risk for severe COVID-19. If you’re at high-risk, it’s time to create a PLAN! If you get COVID, GO speak with your healthcare professional about prescription treatment options! You can visitKNOWPLANGO.com to determine your risk, make a plan and be prepared to take action if COVID-19 strikes in your life. @pfizerinc #PfizerSponsored #KnowPlanGo
